sections.title: Logs concerning the payment service: focusing on transactions

input.value:
fetch logs
| filter matchesValue(dt.entity.process_group_instance, "PROCESS_GROUP_INSTANCE-A05DD343E8C5C1CF") and matchesValue(log.source, "/var/log/pods/prod_paymentservice-6b8dc8c5b6-dwwgm_4a997452-07f6-42b7-baff-3f2f59739f41/server/#.log")
| parse content, "json:j"
| fields timestamp, loglevel, message=j[message], traceid=j[dt.trace_id]
| filter loglevel == "ERROR" or contains(message, "processed")
| parse message, "ld 'USD' double:amount"
| summarize transactions = count(), fails=countIf(loglevel == "ERROR"), avg=avg(amount), revenue=sum(amount)
| fieldsAdd est_lost_revenue = avg*fails

fetch logs
| filter matchesValue(dt.entity.process_group_instance, "PROCESS_GROUP_INSTANCE-A05DD343E8C5C1CF") and matchesValue(log.source, "/var/log/pods/prod_paymentservice-6b8dc8c5b6-dwwgm_4a997452-07f6-42b7-baff-3f2f59739f41/server/#.log")
| parse content, "json:j"
| fields timestamp, loglevel, message=j[message], traceid=j[dt.trace_id]
| filter loglevel == "ERROR" or contains(message, "processed")
| parse message, "ld 'USD' double:amount"
| summarize transactions = count(), fails=countIf(loglevel == "ERROR"), avg=avg(amount), revenue=sum(amount)
| fieldsAdd est_lost_revenue = avg*fails

sections.markdown: # Breaking the silos with lookup commands

input.value:
fetch dt.entity.host
| filter entity.name == "ip-10-0-153-3.ec2.internal"
| lookup [fetch metrics | filter dt.entity.host == "ip-10-0-153-3.ec2.internal" and metric.key == "dt.host.disk.used" | summarize disk_used = avg(value), by:dt.entity.host], sourceField:entityId, lookupfield:dt.entity.host, prefix:"metric."
//| lookup [timeseries avg(dt.host.disk.used), by:dt.entity.host, filter:dt.entity.host == "ip-10-0-153-3.ec2.internal"], sourceField:entityId, lookupfield:dt.entity.host, prefix:"metric."
| lookup [fetch events  | filter event.kind == "DAVIS_PROBLEM" and event.status != "CLOSED" and in(affected_entity,"ip-10-0-153-3.ec2.internal") | summarize count=count() | fieldsAdd host="ip-10-0-153-3.ec2.internal"], sourceField:entityId, lookupfield:host, prefix:"problems.open."
| fields entityName, metric.disk_used, problems.open.count

| lookup [fetch events  | filter event.kind == "DAVIS_PROBLEM" and event.status != "CLOSED" and in(affected_entity,"ip-10-0-153-3.ec2.internal") | summarize count=count() | fieldsAdd host="ip-10-0-153-3.ec2.internal"], sourceField:entityId, lookupfield:host, prefix:"problems.open."
